comments: these types are used in system calls or events, basically they are just strings.

comments1: system calls are called by dialog manager, APP should impl callback 'fnSystemCall(user, msgId, msgJson)' in dialog_api.h
all system calls should be handled in that callback.
and 'dialogResponse(msgId, respJson)' must be called for every system call.
NOTE: this callback is a sync call, so don't block this function in APP!
if a system call takes times to do the job, APP should return 'fnSystemCall' firstly, then call 'dialogResponse' after job done.
system call is send to APP via the param 'msgJson', in json format, for example:
comments2: params obj is optional if this call has no param
APP should retuan another json string to dialog manager, for example:
comments3: result obj is optional if this call has no result. or, you can also pass an empty obj to dialog manager
if results are defined but APP didn't return any result, dialog manager will try to use the defaults values

comments: events are sent to dialog manager by APP via 'dialogEvent(msgJson)' in dialog_api.h
to notify dialog manager that some events are triggered
keep in mind: 1. normal events will be handled in the same thread as dialog!
2. some special events those won't affect dialog/states will be handled interrupt_dialog in another thread.
in this case, set property 'interrupt_dialog' to true(default is true)
